* The functions for escaping need to be fixed.
* Prepared queries.
* Asynchronous query execution.
* Notifications.
* Event API.
* Listen / Notify.
* Use binary data encoding for sending parameters for queries.
* Look up and actually be aware of type OIDs and use that for
  type conversion.
* Consider creating a single buffer with all of the values
  serialized into it, but then give the right pointer into
  that buffer. This would help reduce allocations.
* Do we have to create a <C-pointer> for each parameter for
  the result value of byte-storage-address?
* Example applications.
* Documentation.
* Hook up this library as a backend for the sql-database
  library in Open Dylan.
